{"name": "teslemetry-stream", "metadata": {"name": "teslemetry-stream", "version": "0.4.3", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/Teslemetry/teslemetry_stream", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["aiohttp"], "summary": "Teslemetry Streaming API library for Python", "upload_time": 1733290550}, "documentation": ["# Teslemetry Stream Library\nThis is an asynchronous Python 3 library that connects to the Teslemetry Stream server and provides Tesla Fleet Telemetry using server side events.\n\n## Installation\n\n`pip install teslemetry-stream`\n\n## Usage\n\nThe TeslemetryStream class requires:\n\n- session: an aiohttp.ClientSession\n- access_token: an access token from the [Teslemetry console](https://teslemetry.com/console)\n- One or both:\n  - vin: your Tesla's Vehicle Identification Number\n  - server: The Teslemetry server to connect to\n    - na.teslemetry.com\n    - eu.teslemetry.com\n\nThe full list of possible values are provided in `TeslemetryStream.Fields` and `TeslemetryStream.Alerts`\n\nTo connect, either use `async with` on the instance, call `connect()`, or register an callback with `async_add_listener`, which will connect when added and disconnect when removed.\n\nUsing `connect()` or `listen()` will require you to close the session manually using `close()`.\n\n## Example\nThe following example puts the listening loop in the background, then stopping after 20 seconds.\n```\nasync def main():\n    async with aiohttp.ClientSession() as session:\n        stream = TeslemetryStream(\n            access_token=\"<token>\",\n            vin=\"<vin>\",\n            session=session,\n        )\n        await stream.connect()\n\n        def callback(event):\n            print(event[\"data\"])\n\n        remove = stream.async_add_listener(callback)\n\n        print(\"Running\")\n        await asyncio.sleep(60)\n        remove()\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "teslemetry_stream.const", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "teslemetry_stream.const.IntEnum", "bases": ["int", "Enum"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Integer Enum"]}, {"name": "teslemetry_stream.const.StrEnum", "bases": ["str", "Enum"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["String Enum"]}, {"name": "teslemetry_stream.const.TelemetryFields", "bases": ["StrEnum"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "teslemetry_stream.const.TelemetryFields.AC_CHARGING_ENERGY_IN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "teslemetry_stream.const.TelemetryFields.AC_CHARGING_POWER", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "teslemetry_stream.const.TelemetryFields.AUTO_SEAT_CLIMATE_LEFT", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "teslemetry_stream.const.TelemetryFields.AUTO_SEAT_CLIMATE_RIGHT", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "teslemetry_stream.const.TelemetryFields.AUTOMATIC_BLIND_SPOT_CAMERA", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "teslemetry_stream.const.TelemetryFields.AUTOMATIC_EMERGENCY_BRAKING_OFF", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "teslemetry_stream.const.TelemetryFields.BATTERY_HEATER_ON", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "teslemetry_stream.const.TelemetryFields.BATTERY_LEVEL", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "teslemetry_stream.const.TelemetryFields.BLIND_SPOT_COLLISION_WARNING_CHIME", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "teslemetry_stream.const.TelemetryFields.BMS_FULL_CHARGE_COMPLETE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "teslemetry_stream.const.TelemetryFields.BMS_STATE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "teslemetry_stream.const.TelemetryFields.BRAKE_PEDAL", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name"